Payment Provider Abstraction & Wompi Integration – Locked Specification

Scope

This document fully locks the payment provider abstraction and the Wompi integration for the platform. It is implementation-ready and aligns with previously locked documents (Orders, Roles, API conventions, Observability).

Goals:
	•	Support offline payments (CASH / NEQUI / BANK_TRANSFER) + online PSP (Wompi) for MVP
	•	Provide a pluggable PaymentProvider interface to add providers later
	•	Securely handle webhooks, idempotency, and payment attempt lifecycle
	•	Keep merchants in control; platform does not custody funds

⸻

1) High-level decisions (Locked)
	•	Tenant-scoped PSP config: each tenant can enable/disable Wompi and store credentials in the secret manager; only ADMIN may manage. PAYMENT_SETTINGS_MANAGE governs it.
	•	Order ↔ PaymentAttempt separation: Orders are created from checkout; PaymentAttempts represent attempts to pay an order (provider or offline). PaymentAttempt is the source of truth for payment lifecycle.
	•	Idempotency: idempotency keys accepted for payment creation and enforced server-side.
	•	Webhooks: provider webhooks (Wompi) are authoritative for payment confirmation; webhooks must be verified and processed idempotently.
	•	Refunds: MVP supports full refunds recorded in the system. For Wompi, provider refund API support is implemented if tenant enables it; otherwise refunds are offline and recorded by merchant.

⸻

2) Concepts and Models (Locked)

2.1 Key entities
	•	orders (locked earlier) — business order
	•	payment_attempts — record per attempt to pay an order
	•	payments (optional alias) — ledger entries produced from confirmed attempts
	•	payment_providers — tenant-scoped provider config metadata (not raw secrets)
	•	refunds — refund records (for audit and reconciliation)

2.2 PaymentAttempt fields (locked schema below)
	•	id (UUID)
	•	tenant_id (UUID)
	•	order_id (UUID)
	•	provider (NULL for offline) — e.g., WOMPI or OFFLINE_NEQUI
	•	provider_attempt_id (nullable) — provider-side id (e.g., Wompi transaction id)
	•	status — PENDING | PENDING_PROVIDER | PAID | FAILED | REFUNDED | CANCELLED
	•	amount_cents (int)
	•	currency (char3)
	•	method — NEQUI|BANK_TRANSFER|CASH|WOMPI (string enum)
	•	metadata JSONB — raw provider response or custom fields
	•	idempotency_key (nullable) — dedupe key for creation
	•	created_at, updated_at

2.3 Payment status transitions (locked)
	•	PENDING (created client-side/offline) → PENDING_PROVIDER (when provider session started) → PAID (webhook or manual mark) or FAILED.
	•	Offline methods: PENDING → PAID when merchant marks paid.
	•	Refunds: PAID → REFUNDED when refund recorded/confirmed.

