4) PaymentProvider Interface (Java) — Locked contract

Define a Java interface that all providers implement.

public interface PaymentProvider {
  // start a payment attempt; returns provider-specific client params for frontend
  ProviderPaymentResponse createPaymentAttempt(PaymentAttemptRequest req);

  // Optional: call provider refund API
  ProviderRefundResponse refund(String providerAttemptId, RefundRequest req);

  // Verify webhook signature header + parse payload -> ProviderWebhookEvent
  ProviderWebhookEvent parseAndVerifyWebhook(String rawBody, Map<String,String> headers) throws InvalidSignatureException;
}

ProviderPaymentResponse includes fields used by storefront e.g., clientParams.

Providers must be stateless and idempotent-friendly (service layer enforces idempotency).

