5) Wompi-specific integration (Locked)

5.1 What Wompi provides (context)
	•	Wompi is a Colombian PSP with widget-based client integration and server webhooks indicating payment state.
	•	Wompi requires server-side signature verification for webhooks and provides transaction IDs and statuses.

5.2 Wompi createPaymentAttempt flow (Locked)
	1.	Merchant Admin configures Wompi keys (publicKey + privateKey) via PUT /payments/wompi (already locked in Admin API). Keys stored encrypted in secret manager.
	2.	Frontend calls POST /api/public/v1/checkout/orders/{orderId}/payments with provider=WOMPI.
	3.	Java validates order, amount, tenant, idempotency.
	4.	Java creates payment_attempts row with status=PENDING_PROVIDER and idempotency_key if provided.
	5.	Java calls Wompi API to create a payment session (server-side) or prepares clientParams for widget using publicKey/params signed by server.
	6.	Java returns clientParams in response for storefront to render widget.
	7.	User completes payment in Wompi UI; Wompi sends webhook to your /api/webhooks/wompi.

5.3 Wompi webhook handling (Locked)
	•	Webhook endpoint: POST /api/webhooks/wompi
	•	Verification: validate signature / public key as per Wompi docs (verify X-Wompi-Signature or payload signature). If invalid → 401 and log.
	•	Idempotency: provider event ID deduplicated. Store raw payload in payment_attempts.metadata or separate provider_webhook_logs table.
	•	On transaction event with status APPROVED or AUTHORIZED per Wompi mapping → mark payment_attempts.status = PAID and update provider_attempt_id.
	•	On FAILED/DECLINED → mark FAILED.
	•	Create order_events / audit_events for PAYMENT_CONFIRMED with traceId.

5.4 Security
	•	Restrict webhook endpoint to POST only; validate TLS; check signature header; log sender IP and payload.
	•	Rate limit webhooks to avoid DoS.

5.5 Webhook idempotency & reconciliation
	•	If webhook arrives and payment_attempts already marked PAID, simply acknowledge (200) and no duplicate processing.
	•	If webhook arrives and no matching payment_attempt (edge case), create a reconciliation record and notify ops.

⸻

6) Idempotency & Duplicate Prevention (Locked)
	•	Creation endpoints accept Idempotency-Key header. If present, server checks ux_payment_attempts_idempo_tenant_order and returns existing attempt.
	•	For webhook events, dedupe on provider event_id (store in payment_attempts.metadata or separate provider_events table).
	•	Use DB unique constraints + transactions to avoid races.

⸻

7) Admin Flows (Locked)
	•	Mark order as paid (offline): Merchant Admin action POST /orders/{orderId}/mark-paid creates a payment_attempt with method=NEQUI|BANK_TRANSFER|CASH, status=PAID, provider=null, and records audit event PAYMENT_MARKED_PAID.
	•	Configure Wompi: Admin provides publicKey and privateKey via PUT /payments/wompi. Private key stored encrypted; publicKey stored in DB for reference.
	•	Trigger refund: Admin may call POST /orders/{orderId}/refund. If provider refund enabled and possible, Java calls provider refund API and records refunds row; otherwise merchant records offline refund and records refunds row with method=OFFLINE.

⸻

8) Refunds (Locked behavior)
	•	Only full refunds supported in MVP.
	•	Refunds create a refunds row and update payment_attempts to REFUNDED.
	•	If provider supports refunds via API (Wompi), call provider refund endpoint; ensure idempotency and record provider response.
	•	If provider refund fails or unsupported, merchant performs refund externally, then Admin records refund in Merchant Admin (audit required).

⸻

9) Webhook Endpoint Design (Locked)
	•	Endpoint: POST /api/webhooks/wompi
	•	No auth required other than signature verification
	•	Consume raw body, parse JSON, verify signature, then enqueue processing job (async) for reliability
	•	Return 200 quickly upon acceptance, 4xx on invalid signature
	•	Processing job updates DB, produces order_events, and notifies merchant via Merchant Admin WebSocket/notification (optional)

⸻

10) Observability & Audit (Locked)
	•	Log every provider call with traceId, tenantId, orderId, provider, providerAttemptId
	•	Store raw webhook payload in payment_attempts.metadata or separate provider_webhook_logs for debugging (redact sensitive fields)
	•	Audit events required: PAYMENT_ATTEMPT_CREATED, PAYMENT_CONFIRMED, PAYMENT_FAILED, REFUND_EXECUTED.

⸻

11) Error Handling & Retries (Locked)
	•	For provider API calls, use exponential backoff with jitter (retry 3 times) for transient errors
	•	If provider createPaymentAttempt fails definitively, mark attempt FAILED and surface user-friendly error to frontend
	•	Webhook processing must be idempotent; if processing job fails, schedule retry with dead-letter queue and notify ops

